  "title": "2.3 back in develop for the release",
  "body": " - **breadcrumb widget**: a new widget to visualize the path of a hierarchical menu / navigation\r\n - **range input widget**: an alternative view to the range slider based on inputs (min max)\r\n - *EXPERIMENTAL* dynamically remove and add widgets. This is tagged as experimental because we are trying it extensively, it's a major change in the core of IS.js. It might contains unforeseen edge case bugs. It is used on [Angular-InstantSearch](https://discourse.algolia.com/t/release-of-angular-instantsearch-beta/3731), go check it out if you haven't already.\r\n - **loading indicator**: on mobile, it's really frustrating to not have feedbacks when something goes wrong on the network latency. This adds a new spinner in the SearchBox and the information can be used in any widget.",
